The Democrats Back Down
The decision by congressional Democrats to relent on their demand for a 
      troop withdrawal date from Iraq was seen by the morning newspapers as a defeat for anti-war lawmakers and a rare 
      victory for the White House.
      And why choosing a 
      hospital could be a life or death decision. 
 Joel Roberts has the highlights of the day's 
      headlines.  More...
